WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:02.735
That trial
was 10 lifetimes ago.

00:02.737 --> 00:05.404
She accused him
of that murder.

00:05.406 --> 00:07.672
She took it back, Jay.

00:07.674 --> 00:09.641
It<i> is</i> the truth.

00:11.278 --> 00:13.812
Fauna: I need to talk to you
about my real mother.

00:13.814 --> 00:15.614
Corinna: I used to
call her "Apate" --

00:15.616 --> 00:17.882
the goddess of deceit.

00:17.884 --> 00:19.251
[ Woman screams ]

00:22.222 --> 00:24.222
You saved my life.

00:24.224 --> 00:25.490
I just want the truth.

00:25.492 --> 00:27.025
Tamar is in Hawaii.

00:27.027 --> 00:29.695
You get me a plane ticket,
and we can talk to her together.

00:30.965 --> 00:33.498
Psychiatrist: Well,
I did take note that, uh,

00:33.500 --> 00:36.034
she exhibited delusions
of grandeur

00:36.036 --> 00:39.171
and was given to the telling
of fantastic tales,

00:39.173 --> 00:41.706
which had little or no basis
in fact.

00:41.708 --> 00:44.442
We call this, uh,
delirium's dementia,

00:44.444 --> 00:47.445
which is common in hysterics.

00:47.447 --> 00:50.515
Much of her, um,
abnormal behavior

00:50.517 --> 00:53.852
has to do with, uh,
her mania for sex.

00:53.854 --> 00:57.322
Um, even, um, at 14.

00:57.324 --> 00:59.458
Even as young as 11 years old,

00:59.460 --> 01:03.662
as her father and others
have testified.

01:03.664 --> 01:07.132
Neeb Jr.: And in your
professional opinion,

01:07.134 --> 01:09.133
why would that happen?

01:09.135 --> 01:11.203
The Electra Complex
is a young girl's

01:11.205 --> 01:13.872
psycho-sexual competition
with her mother,

01:13.874 --> 01:18.142
or in this case, stepmother,
to become the dominant female.

01:18.144 --> 01:23.948
In Tamar's fantasy life,
she supplants the mother.

01:23.950 --> 01:28.620
We've seen how Tamar is obsessed
with her father.

01:28.622 --> 01:31.356
And he is an impressive man,
after all.

01:31.358 --> 01:34.292
But in her poor, deluded mind,

01:34.294 --> 01:38.897
the things that she dreamed
and desired became real.

01:38.899 --> 01:43.635
Tamar even claimed
that Dr. Hodel

01:43.637 --> 01:45.303
was the Black Dahlia Killer.

01:45.305 --> 01:47.105
[ Laughter ]

01:47.107 --> 01:50.308
Well, perhaps he's
the Lindbergh baby, too.

01:50.310 --> 01:53.245
[ Laughter ]

01:53.247 --> 02:02.787
♪♪

02:02.789 --> 02:12.197
♪♪

02:12.199 --> 02:21.473
♪♪

02:21.475 --> 02:30.949
♪♪

02:30.951 --> 02:36.889
♪♪

02:36.891 --> 02:39.491
[ Mid-tempo jazz music plays ]

02:39.493 --> 02:43.027
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:43.029 --> 02:45.230
What? What?
Here I come bearing gifts,
my liege.

02:45.232 --> 02:47.299
Oh, no. This makes me --
That makes me very nervous.

02:47.301 --> 02:49.634
I apologized to King Eddy.
I'm back in the fold.

02:49.636 --> 02:52.705
What are you -- What --
Do I even ask?
You wanted to
have Life Savers.

02:52.707 --> 02:54.839
Oh, God, what --
You're my favorite
life saver.

02:54.841 --> 02:56.508
500 of the best words
you've ever read

02:56.510 --> 02:59.043
on the framing of
an innocent man.
Okay, what --
what is this?

02:59.045 --> 03:01.980
Why do I feel like there's
some big, terrible "and"...
With my notes.
Fact-check away.

03:01.982 --> 03:04.382
...looming here?

03:04.384 --> 03:05.918
I found her.

03:05.920 --> 03:08.520
Who? You f--
You found who, Jay?

03:08.522 --> 03:11.256
Tamar Hodel.
The daughter.

03:11.258 --> 03:12.657
I found her again, baby.

03:12.659 --> 03:14.259
That is not all.
[ Chuckles ]

03:14.261 --> 03:15.794
What?
Hey, Shell-Shocked.

03:15.796 --> 03:17.796
Okay. All right.
Here, why would I even care?

03:17.798 --> 03:19.664
That's not big enough, Jay.

03:19.666 --> 03:21.800
Peter, things are shaping up.
Things are shaping up.

03:21.802 --> 03:23.401
It's like --
It's coalescing.

03:23.403 --> 03:25.070
It's -- It's -- It's --
It's feeling

03:25.072 --> 03:26.939
a lot more like proof,
like a smoking gun.

03:26.941 --> 03:29.341
Oh, a lot like proof,
he says.

03:29.343 --> 03:32.010
Imagine -- Imagine every crazy
thing she said was true.

03:32.012 --> 03:33.946
Just stop and think about it.
Stop and think about it.

03:33.948 --> 03:35.748
She said that her dad
was the Black Dahlia Killer.
Mm. Mm.

03:35.750 --> 03:37.482
No one believed her.
They laughed at her.

03:37.484 --> 03:39.284
But the cops always like the guy
that had a medical background.

03:39.286 --> 03:41.686
No, Jay, listen to me. It would
have to be the A-bomb, okay?

03:41.688 --> 03:43.822
Not "like,"
not "something like."
You want the A-bomb?
I'll give you the A-bomb.

03:43.824 --> 03:47.425
I found
Tamar Hodel's daughter.

03:47.427 --> 03:49.561
Fauna Hodel.
Her name's Fauna Hodel.

03:49.563 --> 03:51.830
I found her. And the dates --
The dates, Peter.
Wait.

03:51.832 --> 03:53.832
What?
Th-They work out.
They work out.

03:53.834 --> 03:55.968
Daughter?
Tamar had a daughter.

03:55.970 --> 03:58.637
That's why they sent her away --
the convent.

03:58.639 --> 04:00.639
They sent her away.
She gave up the baby.

04:00.641 --> 04:02.707
She ran off to Hawaii.
Daughter?

04:02.709 --> 04:04.643
Tamar's daughter?
Oh, shit!
Yes, yes!

04:04.645 --> 04:06.244
Are you telling me --
Excuse me.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.380
That's exa-- What?!
What?! What do you want?!
Okay. Okay.

04:08.382 --> 04:10.315
What do you want?!
I can't give you what you want.
I cannot fight you.

04:10.317 --> 04:11.984
All right, he didn't
do anything.
I can't fight you.

04:11.986 --> 04:13.385
It's enough. It's enough.
It's enough.
I want to.

04:13.387 --> 04:14.919
We did this already.
Talk to me.

04:14.921 --> 04:17.322
Finish the thought.
Sit down and finish the thought.

04:17.324 --> 04:19.191
Are you messing with me here?
Huh?
I'm not messing
with you at all.

04:19.193 --> 04:20.993
Are you shooting me straight?
I'm shooting you straight.

04:20.995 --> 04:22.861
The daughter -- the
granddaughter -- the daughter.

04:22.863 --> 04:24.863
Yes, yes, that's exactly
what I'm talking about.
Because that is good.

04:24.865 --> 04:26.264
Exactly. It is good.
That could be something.

04:26.266 --> 04:28.533
Yeah!
Just leave
the bogeyman shit out.

04:28.535 --> 04:30.135
Deal.

04:30.137 --> 04:33.138
Now I need --
I need two tickets to Hawaii,

04:33.140 --> 04:34.606
because that's
where she's at.

04:34.608 --> 04:36.008
No, no. Don't laugh.
Don't laugh.

04:36.010 --> 04:37.810
This is real, Peter.
Two tickets to Hawaii.

04:37.812 --> 04:40.679
I'm gonna take her daughter
to Hawaii to get her talking.

04:40.681 --> 04:43.081
I'm gonna -- If I give her
her long, lost daughter,

04:43.083 --> 04:45.283
I've got the story.
What is this, a game show?

04:45.285 --> 04:47.952
What's behind door number two,
Jay? Look at me.

04:47.954 --> 04:50.222
Look at me in the eye
and tell me you got the A-bomb.

04:50.224 --> 04:52.357
I got the A-bomb.
That's what I'm telling you.

04:52.359 --> 04:54.426
I got the nuke,
and it is primed and ready.

04:54.428 --> 04:56.362
You send me.

04:57.431 --> 05:01.233
You're a tremendous liar,
and I'm gonna do it.

05:01.235 --> 05:03.836
So take enough rope
to hang yourself.

05:03.838 --> 05:05.704
No per diem.
No room and board.

05:05.706 --> 05:06.905
[ Laughs ]

05:06.907 --> 05:08.773
And I'm gonna
have to tell somebody,

05:08.775 --> 05:10.242
so you have to show up
with something.

05:10.244 --> 05:12.044
You've got to come up
with something, okay?

05:12.046 --> 05:14.046
You're not gonna regret this,
Peter.
I regret it right now.

05:14.048 --> 05:16.581
Remember where you are.
Remember Emperor Trajan?

05:16.583 --> 05:17.982
Love the guy.
Miss him every day.

05:17.984 --> 05:20.118
Emperor Trajan was betrayed
by his own men, okay?

05:20.120 --> 05:21.653
Buried up to his neck
in sand.

05:21.655 --> 05:24.923
His counselor Vespasian said
to him, "Memento quo nunc es."

05:24.925 --> 05:28.593
"Remember where you are."

05:28.595 --> 05:31.196
[ Chuckles ]

05:31.198 --> 05:33.131
Can I go?

05:33.133 --> 05:34.533
Yeah, go. Go.

05:34.535 --> 05:36.869
You want a lei?
I'm gonna send you a lei.
Go.

05:36.871 --> 05:39.171
[ Dog barks ]

05:42.743 --> 05:45.878
Jimmy Lee: Fauna.

05:45.880 --> 05:48.747
Come on, now. We have
just enough time to
eat before the bus.

05:48.749 --> 05:50.815
Yeah, Mama.

05:50.817 --> 05:52.885
You all set to come home now,
right?

05:52.887 --> 05:55.354
No more of that attitude.

05:55.356 --> 05:56.621
Yes, Mama.

05:56.623 --> 05:58.022
Okay.

05:58.024 --> 06:00.292
Somebody's at the door for you,
Fauna.

06:00.294 --> 06:01.493
A white man.

06:01.495 --> 06:04.596
Knows who you are
and everything.

06:09.103 --> 06:11.303
[ Footsteps
rapidly approaching ]

06:11.305 --> 06:13.638
Who the hell are you?

06:13.640 --> 06:15.774
M-Mama, I know him.
He's a friend.

06:15.776 --> 06:17.776
Oh, goodness.
A friend?

06:17.778 --> 06:20.312
Fauna,
I've got the tickets.
Show me.

06:20.314 --> 06:22.781
What the hell is this?

06:22.783 --> 06:24.583
Those are mine.
Tickets.

06:24.585 --> 06:26.919
[ Chuckles ]
To Hawaii?
Mm-hmm.

06:26.921 --> 06:28.520
I don't know who the hell
you think you are,

06:28.522 --> 06:30.455
but you're not taking
that child nowhere.

06:30.457 --> 06:32.190
So take the damn tickets
to Hawaii...
Mama!

06:32.192 --> 06:33.858
...and get the hell
out this house!
You better --

06:33.860 --> 06:35.060
Mama, I can't believe
you just did that!

06:35.062 --> 06:36.595
You come around here again,

06:36.597 --> 06:38.731
I will call the law
and have your ass arrested.

06:38.733 --> 06:41.199
She is 16 years old.

06:41.201 --> 06:43.268
Ma'am, t-this --
this is absolutely

06:43.270 --> 06:44.736
not -- not
what it looks like.

06:44.738 --> 06:45.938
What's it look like, asshole?
It looks bad.

06:45.940 --> 06:47.405
Yeah?
But just -- I'm --

06:47.407 --> 06:49.073
You think this is my first trip
to L.A.?

06:49.075 --> 06:50.743
Huh? You think I'm
as dumb as she is?!
No.

06:50.745 --> 06:53.278
Mama.
Shut up, Fauna!

06:53.280 --> 06:54.813
You know what, Mama?
I'm looking for Tamar.

06:54.815 --> 06:56.548
I'm looking
for my real mother.

06:56.550 --> 06:58.216
Tina: Ohh...

06:58.218 --> 07:00.953
[ Dogs barking ]

07:00.955 --> 07:04.289
How many times
I've got to tell you

07:04.291 --> 07:06.625
that you have got
to be careful?

07:06.627 --> 07:08.560
You know what, Mama? When are
you gonna tell me the truth?

07:08.562 --> 07:10.295
I ain't dumb,
like you keep saying!

07:10.297 --> 07:12.564
What do you know?
You looking real dumb
right now!

07:12.566 --> 07:14.299
Can you get more of those?
Can you get more of those?!
You don't know
who that man is!

07:14.301 --> 07:16.301
You don't know
who that man is!

07:16.303 --> 07:18.036
What the hell is
wrong with you?!

07:18.038 --> 07:19.371
Can you get more?
Yeah. I have the receipts.

07:19.373 --> 07:20.973
It's just paper.
What time's the flight?

07:20.975 --> 07:22.907
It leaves in two hours.
We have to go.

07:22.909 --> 07:25.177
Two hours?
Mama, put the knife down, Mama.

07:25.179 --> 07:26.845
Mama, put that knife down!
Shut up!

07:26.847 --> 07:28.380
[ Indistinct shouting ]

07:28.382 --> 07:30.248
Plane leaves in two hours!
Get on out of here!

07:30.250 --> 07:34.519
And you! I will braid a switch
and whip your fast ass!

07:34.521 --> 07:36.288
You -- Ohh!

07:37.724 --> 07:39.591
[ Chuckles ]

07:39.593 --> 07:41.259
I'm with you on this one,
Jimmy.

07:41.261 --> 07:44.963
That girl gonna get herself
into a whole lot of trouble.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.743
♪♪

07:58.745 --> 08:00.945
Shit. She's gone.
Fauna!

08:00.947 --> 08:02.747
[ Engine starts ]
Fauna!

08:02.749 --> 08:05.083
[ Tires screech ]
Fauna!

08:05.085 --> 08:07.285
Fauna!

08:07.287 --> 08:10.489
♪♪

08:10.491 --> 08:12.957
[ Door closes ]

08:12.959 --> 08:15.293
Goddamn it.

08:15.295 --> 08:24.236
♪♪

08:24.238 --> 08:33.378
♪♪

08:33.380 --> 08:42.187
♪♪

08:42.189 --> 08:50.795
♪♪

08:50.797 --> 08:56.735
♪♪

08:56.737 --> 08:59.471
[ Birds chirping ]

08:59.473 --> 09:08.413
♪♪

09:08.415 --> 09:12.785
Lokelanai Road. Yeah.
I think we're close.

09:15.155 --> 09:18.257
It really is something.

09:20.294 --> 09:23.495
I can see why -- why my mother
wanted to be here.

09:23.497 --> 09:26.098
Yeah, it's great, but we should,
uh -- We should get moving.

09:26.100 --> 09:28.500
Heaven must look
like this.

09:28.502 --> 09:33.339
I didn't know you could see
so far, so much.

09:35.109 --> 09:38.510
I didn't know
the ocean was so big.

09:38.512 --> 09:43.115
♪♪

09:43.117 --> 09:45.450
What am I gonna say
when I see her?

09:45.452 --> 09:48.053
It doesn't matter.
She'll be happy to see you.

09:48.055 --> 09:50.655
[ Car door opens ]
Come on.

09:50.657 --> 09:52.991
[ Car door closes ]

09:52.993 --> 09:56.362
Shoot.
I've got so many questions.

09:59.400 --> 10:02.034
[ Birds chirping ]

10:22.889 --> 10:25.089
[ Engine shuts off ]

10:25.091 --> 10:28.093
[ Chirping continues ]

10:32.499 --> 10:34.767
[ Car door closes ]

10:34.769 --> 10:36.635
This is it?

10:36.637 --> 10:39.237
12 Lokelanai Road?

10:39.239 --> 10:41.440
[ Car door closes ]
This is it.

10:43.243 --> 10:46.779
I don't know any Tamar,
but look back there.

10:46.781 --> 10:48.913
Are you sure?

10:48.915 --> 10:50.649
Yeah, go ahead.

10:50.651 --> 10:53.318
I hold mail for all kinds
of people around here.

10:53.320 --> 10:57.990
Sometimes letters sit there for
a few months, sometimes forever.

11:06.200 --> 11:08.400
So how do you know
who is who?

11:08.402 --> 11:10.535
Don't take what isn't yours,
friend.

11:10.537 --> 11:12.737
[ Chuckles ]

11:12.739 --> 11:14.339
Yep.

11:14.341 --> 11:15.740
[ Thunder rumbles ]

11:15.742 --> 11:17.409
Damn it.

11:17.411 --> 11:19.511
[ Convertible roof whirring ]

11:26.353 --> 11:27.686
[ Sighs ]
[ Car door closes ]

11:27.688 --> 11:29.954
The most expensive sunglasses
in Hawaii.

11:29.956 --> 11:31.857
Here.

11:33.694 --> 11:36.094
Cheer up. We'll find her.
It's an island, right?

11:36.096 --> 11:37.962
She can't be
too far away.

11:37.964 --> 11:39.431
She doesn't
want to see me.

11:39.433 --> 11:40.965
Yes, she does.

11:40.967 --> 11:43.101
No, she doesn't.
Come on. Fauna...

11:43.103 --> 11:44.503
Well, it's true.

11:44.505 --> 11:46.304
You know, she gave me away
for a reason.

11:46.306 --> 11:48.773
Because she was -- she was too
young. That's the reason.

11:48.775 --> 11:50.876
Well, why is she hiding?

11:52.379 --> 11:54.646
She's not hiding from you,
I can tell you that much.

11:54.648 --> 11:56.314
What do you mean?

11:56.316 --> 11:58.383
All I mean is, she could be
hiding from anybody,

11:58.385 --> 11:59.852
from a bad boyfriend,
from a relative.

11:59.854 --> 12:02.254
She doesn't want to answer
questions from a reporter

12:02.256 --> 12:03.455
about what her father did.

12:03.457 --> 12:05.390
We're gonna find your mother.
Don't worry.

12:05.392 --> 12:06.725
What did
my grandfather do?

12:06.727 --> 12:09.994
He ran an illegal abortion
clinic, like I told.

12:09.996 --> 12:12.064
You know what?
Here. Trade.

12:12.066 --> 12:14.533
What do you think
about this?

12:14.535 --> 12:17.736
♪♪

12:17.738 --> 12:19.538
[ Laughs ]
[ Engine starts ]

12:21.809 --> 12:23.909
[ Coin clinks, jukebox whirs ]

12:23.911 --> 12:26.244
What's that drink you ordered?
An Arnold...

12:26.246 --> 12:28.180
Palmer?
Great golfer.

12:28.182 --> 12:29.447
It's a hell of a drink.

12:29.449 --> 12:31.316
It's half, uh, iced-tea,
half-lemonade.

12:31.318 --> 12:33.451
I think you'll like it.
Kind of bitter, kind of sweet.

12:33.453 --> 12:35.521
Ha. Like you?

12:35.523 --> 12:37.956
Exactly like me.

12:38.926 --> 12:40.992
[ Laughter ]

12:40.994 --> 12:42.260
Grab him.

12:42.262 --> 12:45.063
Ohh! Hawaii.

12:45.065 --> 12:47.933
I haven't
been here in...

12:47.935 --> 12:49.935
I came back --

12:49.937 --> 12:55.140
Well, I came here on my way
back, uh, from not here, but...

12:55.142 --> 12:57.809
Hawaii,
generally speaking.

12:57.811 --> 12:59.745
Back from where?

12:59.747 --> 13:01.479
From Korea.

13:01.481 --> 13:03.348
You a soldier?
Mm.

13:03.350 --> 13:08.354
I remember walking through
Honolulu thinking,

13:08.356 --> 13:11.823
"They should've trained us
how to come back," you know?

13:11.825 --> 13:14.893
They teach us how to fight,
then bury us in the shit,

13:14.895 --> 13:18.964
and they never show you
how to come back.

13:18.966 --> 13:20.232
There she is.

13:20.234 --> 13:22.234
Two Arnold Palmers.
Burger coming.

13:22.236 --> 13:23.769
Young lady,
I got a question for you.

13:23.771 --> 13:26.038
Do you know a Tamar?
Tamar Hodel?

13:26.040 --> 13:27.773
Naaw. Mnh-mnh.

13:27.775 --> 13:29.575
Where do, uh,

13:29.577 --> 13:32.444
the people live that get
their mail from Tico?

13:32.446 --> 13:35.647
Well, Tico takes mail to
all kind of people on boats,

13:35.649 --> 13:39.050
but there's a bunch living
by the beach on Waikitea,

13:39.052 --> 13:40.919
just south.
Waikitea?

13:40.921 --> 13:42.120
Mm-hmm.

13:42.122 --> 13:44.055
Living here
must be wonderful.

13:44.057 --> 13:45.657
Aloha.

13:45.659 --> 13:47.659
What are these people?

13:47.661 --> 13:50.262
I'm just excited,
I guess.

13:50.264 --> 13:53.265
I can't shake the feeling that
she's gonna look in my eyes,

13:53.267 --> 13:56.735
and it's all
gonna make sense.

13:56.737 --> 13:58.670
♪♪

13:58.672 --> 14:00.673
Yeah, I get that.

14:02.542 --> 14:04.009
Aloha.

14:04.011 --> 14:05.877
Aloha.

14:05.879 --> 14:08.280
♪♪

14:08.282 --> 14:10.015
I'm gonna go
to the bathroom.

14:10.017 --> 14:11.216
You all right?
Yeah.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.419
[ Indistinct talking ]

14:13.421 --> 14:14.752
Hey, you, come on.

14:14.754 --> 14:16.354
Come on.
[ Pounds on table ]

14:16.356 --> 14:17.956
Yeah?
I'm the f--

14:17.958 --> 14:19.224
Don't do it.
Go for it.

14:19.226 --> 14:21.026
That's it. You see that?
She was looking at him.

14:21.028 --> 14:22.628
Go, go.

14:22.630 --> 14:24.029
[ Laughter ]

14:24.031 --> 14:25.363
[ Coin clinks ]

14:25.365 --> 14:27.299
[ Jukebox whirs ]

14:27.301 --> 14:28.967
♪ iUno, dos! ♪

14:28.969 --> 14:30.368
♪ One, two, tres, quatro! ♪

14:30.370 --> 14:32.638
That rascal
left you all alone?

14:32.640 --> 14:35.441
What are you doing by yourself?
You're the prettiest girl
in the joint.

14:35.443 --> 14:38.043
Come on,
dance with me.
♪ Wooly bully ♪

14:38.045 --> 14:40.045
No, my -- my friend
is gonna be back.
Come on, dance with me.

14:40.047 --> 14:41.713
No, I --
I think I should stay.
Come on.

14:41.715 --> 14:43.381
Come on,
dance with me.
I'm sorry.

14:43.383 --> 14:44.983
Come on. You're --
You're a dancer.
No.

14:44.985 --> 14:46.785
I'm a dancer.
Listen, I-I d--

14:46.787 --> 14:49.254
Let's just dance.
I don't think
this is a good idea.

14:49.256 --> 14:50.588
My friend
is gonna be back soon.

14:50.590 --> 14:52.057
No big deal,
it's just one dance.

14:52.059 --> 14:54.326
Come on, don't be cruel.
Don't be cruel.

14:54.328 --> 14:56.328
I really don't --
Come on!

14:56.330 --> 14:57.996
Just one dance. That's all.

14:57.998 --> 14:59.131
You and me, yeah.
Ooh.

14:59.133 --> 15:01.266
I think she's all right.

15:01.268 --> 15:04.402
Just got off six months
in the Big Blue.
♪ Had two big horns ♪

15:04.404 --> 15:06.338
It's all right, pal.
I get it.

15:06.340 --> 15:07.939
♪ And a wooly jaw ♪

15:07.941 --> 15:09.341
♪ Wooly bully ♪

15:09.343 --> 15:11.409
[ Indistinct yelling ]
Don't worry about it.

15:11.411 --> 15:13.011
Donna: Y'all guys better not
start nothing in here.

15:13.013 --> 15:14.880
We're not gonna start anything.
We're not gonna start anything.

15:14.882 --> 15:16.682
Jay, Jay, I think
we got to go now.
♪ Wooly bully ♪

15:16.684 --> 15:18.350
♪ Wooly bully, wooly bully ♪
What are you gonna do?

15:18.352 --> 15:20.152
What are you gonna do?
What are you doing?

15:20.154 --> 15:21.687
Jay.
All right.

15:21.689 --> 15:24.022
Jay...
will you listen to me?
♪ Hatty told Matty ♪

15:24.024 --> 15:26.224
I'm just making sure
we don't get in a fight.
You're doing something.

15:26.226 --> 15:27.693
♪ Let's don't take no chance ♪

15:27.695 --> 15:29.094
Huh?
♪ Let's not be L-7 ♪

15:29.096 --> 15:30.896
Jackass!
You gonna take that?

15:30.898 --> 15:33.165
♪ Come and learn to dance ♪
Yo, shitbird.

15:33.167 --> 15:35.901
If we're not dancing,
we're fighting.
♪ Wooly bully ♪

15:35.903 --> 15:37.703
All right.

15:37.705 --> 15:39.437
Hey! Hey!

15:39.439 --> 15:41.239
Put that down!
Put it down.
♪ Wooly bully ♪

15:41.241 --> 15:43.575
Put it down before
I stick it up your ass.
♪ Wooly bully ♪

15:43.577 --> 15:46.845
All right.
♪ Wooly bully, watch it, now,
watch it, watch it, watch it ♪

15:46.847 --> 15:49.247
♪♪

15:49.249 --> 15:51.049
♪ Ahh ♪

15:51.051 --> 15:53.719
[ Engine shuts off ]
Fauna: You were looking
to fight all those guys.

15:53.721 --> 15:55.987
No, not all of them.

15:55.989 --> 15:58.857
You were looking
to get your ass kicked.

15:58.859 --> 16:01.293
[ Insects chirping ]

16:04.064 --> 16:05.431
Hello?

16:17.144 --> 16:19.010
Um...

16:19.012 --> 16:20.879
Um...

16:20.881 --> 16:23.215
Yeah, I'll sleep
in the car.
What?

16:23.217 --> 16:26.084
Yeah.
I like sleeping in cars.

16:26.086 --> 16:33.691
♪ While I'm far away
from you, my baby ♪

16:33.693 --> 16:40.298
♪ I know it's hard
for you, my baby ♪

16:40.300 --> 16:45.437
♪ Because it's hard
for me, my baby ♪

16:45.439 --> 16:47.038
Any service in this joint?

16:47.040 --> 16:52.778
♪ And the darkest hour
is just before dawn ♪

16:52.780 --> 17:00.586
♪ Each night before
you go to bed, my baby ♪

17:00.588 --> 17:07.459
♪ Whisper a little prayer
for me, my baby ♪

17:07.461 --> 17:14.065
♪ And tell all the stars above ♪

17:14.067 --> 17:17.669
♪ This is dedicated
to the one I love ♪

17:17.671 --> 17:19.204
♪ This is dedicated ♪

17:19.206 --> 17:21.006
♪ To the one I love ♪

17:21.008 --> 17:25.010
♪ This is dedicated
to the one I love ♪

17:25.012 --> 17:26.344
Wake up.

17:26.346 --> 17:28.614
Hmm? What?

17:28.616 --> 17:30.015
What?

17:30.017 --> 17:31.683
What? Are you okay?

17:31.685 --> 17:32.884
Are you okay?

17:32.886 --> 17:35.020
Yeah.
You were screaming.

17:35.022 --> 17:36.955
I was? Uh...

17:36.957 --> 17:39.758
You -- you heard me --
you heard me scream?

17:39.760 --> 17:42.961
What were you
dreaming about?

17:42.963 --> 17:46.231
[ Rain falling ]

17:46.233 --> 17:48.801
I don't remember.

17:59.647 --> 18:01.913
It wasn't your fault.

18:01.915 --> 18:04.382
What wasn't?

18:04.384 --> 18:07.252
That man -- Sepp.

18:07.254 --> 18:09.688
You did
what you had to do.

18:14.061 --> 18:16.462
Yeah, maybe.

18:18.132 --> 18:20.332
He would've killed us.

18:20.334 --> 18:22.801
God will forgive you.

18:24.271 --> 18:26.472
God, huh?

18:29.076 --> 18:31.377
Yeah.

18:39.153 --> 18:42.554
They never talked about
how good it would feel.

18:42.556 --> 18:49.828
♪♪

18:49.830 --> 18:52.230
They would never
tell you that.

18:52.232 --> 18:54.766
♪♪

18:54.768 --> 19:01.106
It's like...riding in the
chariot of the sun god.

19:01.108 --> 19:05.577
♪♪

19:05.579 --> 19:09.247
One thing I never expect...

19:09.249 --> 19:12.317
♪♪

19:12.319 --> 19:14.853
...to enjoy it.

19:14.855 --> 19:18.590
You know the one thing
I learned in Korea?

19:18.592 --> 19:20.392
Good never wins.

19:20.394 --> 19:22.794
Right and wrong?

19:22.796 --> 19:26.064
I could barely make out
dead from alive.

19:26.066 --> 19:29.201
Talked to a dead guy
for 10 minutes. He was...

19:29.203 --> 19:32.404
[ Laughs ] He was...

19:32.406 --> 19:35.207
Uh, he was frozen.

19:35.209 --> 19:38.276
♪♪

19:38.278 --> 19:40.546
How are you supposed to
make out right from wrong

19:40.548 --> 19:43.215
in a place like that?

19:43.217 --> 19:47.753
♪♪

19:47.755 --> 19:50.288
And you pay a price.
They own you.

19:50.290 --> 19:54.692
You take a life...
and they come with you.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.429
They come with you
forever...

19:57.431 --> 20:02.368
♪♪

20:02.370 --> 20:06.238
...like little...

20:06.240 --> 20:10.642
♪♪

20:10.644 --> 20:13.979
[ Sighs ]
...splinters in the heart.

20:13.981 --> 20:19.785
♪♪

20:19.787 --> 20:23.855
I'm only breathing right now
because of what you did.

20:23.857 --> 20:27.859
♪♪

20:27.861 --> 20:30.562
I don't care how
it made you feel.

20:33.400 --> 20:35.100
[ Car door slams ]

20:38.873 --> 20:45.610
♪♪

20:45.612 --> 20:47.980
[ Knock on door ]

20:51.017 --> 20:54.219
Hey, do you
have a sewing kit?

20:54.221 --> 20:55.554
Yes, sir.

20:55.556 --> 20:58.223
I just, uh --
Do you mind doing me a favor?

20:58.225 --> 21:01.359
My stitches are itching
the crap out of me.

21:01.361 --> 21:02.561
Can you take them out?

21:02.563 --> 21:05.029
Just hold still,
all right?

21:05.031 --> 21:08.166
Hold still,
or it'll hurt.

21:08.168 --> 21:09.835
Agh!

21:10.971 --> 21:12.304
There.
All right, fine.

21:12.306 --> 21:14.239
Thanks.
Five minutes.

21:14.241 --> 21:23.248
♪♪

21:23.250 --> 21:32.224
♪♪

21:34.194 --> 21:35.660
[ Car door closes ]

21:35.662 --> 21:38.062
[ Children shouting ]

21:38.064 --> 21:42.467
We could keep driving, but I'm
not sure we'd make it out alive.

21:42.469 --> 21:46.538
♪♪

21:46.540 --> 21:48.673
Well,
there's nothing here.

21:48.675 --> 21:50.943
Boy: Let go!

21:50.945 --> 21:53.946
Fauna!
Give it to me!

21:53.948 --> 21:56.148
Come on!

21:56.150 --> 21:58.717
Fauna, let it go!

21:59.820 --> 22:02.487
[ Grunts ]
Come on! Come on!

22:02.489 --> 22:03.688
Let go!

22:03.690 --> 22:05.424
Hey...

22:05.426 --> 22:08.092
Is your name Fauna?

22:08.094 --> 22:10.429
Hey, wait.

22:10.431 --> 22:12.364
Wait!

22:12.366 --> 22:21.506
♪♪

22:21.508 --> 22:30.515
♪♪

22:30.517 --> 22:35.320
♪♪

22:35.322 --> 22:37.589
It's gonna be all right.

22:37.591 --> 22:39.591
You don't know that.

22:39.593 --> 22:42.261
[ Breathing heavily ]

22:43.397 --> 22:45.197
[ Chickens clucking ]

22:45.199 --> 22:46.465
[ Sheep bleats ]

22:46.467 --> 22:55.273
♪♪

22:55.275 --> 23:04.349
♪♪

23:04.351 --> 23:13.692
♪♪

23:13.694 --> 23:18.831
♪♪

23:18.833 --> 23:23.936
When you were born,
they never let me hold you.

23:25.572 --> 23:27.840
The nurse let me see you.

23:27.842 --> 23:30.375
I'll never forget that face.
[ Chuckles ]

23:30.377 --> 23:32.911
You're still so beautiful.

23:35.782 --> 23:38.983
They told me that
I'd never see you,

23:38.985 --> 23:43.255
so it would be best if
I never even held you.

23:43.257 --> 23:46.791
[ Voice breaking ]
Can I hold you now?

23:46.793 --> 23:55.667
♪♪

23:55.669 --> 23:59.471
♪♪

23:59.473 --> 24:00.939
Can I call you "mother"?

24:00.941 --> 24:03.675
Oh, no, all of my children
call me Tamar.

24:03.677 --> 24:08.080
♪♪

24:08.082 --> 24:10.815
Tamar, uh...

24:10.817 --> 24:13.351
what happened?

24:13.353 --> 24:15.821
Oh, Fauna.

24:17.291 --> 24:19.157
What happened?

24:19.159 --> 24:22.294
Who is my father?
Was he Negro?

24:24.164 --> 24:26.030
No.

24:26.032 --> 24:29.501
I'm sorry.
You aren't.

24:29.503 --> 24:31.770
I wish you were.

24:31.772 --> 24:35.373
♪♪

24:35.375 --> 24:38.510
[ Muffled ]

24:38.512 --> 24:46.985
♪♪

24:46.987 --> 24:49.387
...they despised all
of us unwed mothers.

24:49.389 --> 24:51.924
There was no God
in that place.

24:54.461 --> 25:00.065
I put Negro on your birth
certificate as your father

25:00.067 --> 25:04.069
because I just wanted you
to belong.

25:05.739 --> 25:08.941
I admire black people
so much.

25:08.943 --> 25:11.410
Every white person
I know was a liar.

25:11.412 --> 25:14.613
And black people
were nice to me.

25:14.615 --> 25:17.816
In the news,
they fought for justice,

25:17.818 --> 25:20.485
for equality,
they know right and wrong.

25:20.487 --> 25:23.355
The name Fauna

25:23.357 --> 25:27.159
comes from a Robinson Jeffers
poem that I just adored.

25:27.161 --> 25:31.930
I even used it again because
I thought I'd never see you.

25:35.702 --> 25:38.370
So who's my father, then?

25:38.372 --> 25:40.505
Oh.

25:40.507 --> 25:42.174
I pushed his memory away

25:42.176 --> 25:44.576
because our understanding levels
were so different.

25:44.578 --> 25:48.046
Please, Tamar, what is
all this lying about?

25:48.048 --> 25:50.114
Don't do this, Fauna.

25:50.116 --> 25:52.451
You're ruining
our perfect moment.

25:52.453 --> 25:53.652
Don't you see?

25:53.654 --> 25:56.321
It's selfish.
Don't do that!

25:56.323 --> 25:58.390
Well, why did Corinna
tell me you were dead?

25:58.392 --> 26:00.859
She hates me because of
what I said at the trial.

26:00.861 --> 26:03.662
Trial? What trial?

26:03.664 --> 26:06.865
♪♪

26:06.867 --> 26:08.400
Oh.

26:10.604 --> 26:12.805
She didn't tell you?

26:14.341 --> 26:16.475
Tell me what?

26:18.278 --> 26:21.746
Right before you were born,
there was a trial.

26:21.748 --> 26:24.516
It was terrible.

26:27.087 --> 26:28.887
What kind of trial?

26:28.889 --> 26:33.558
Oh, it was a "morals" trial
with my father, George Hodel.

26:33.560 --> 26:36.628
Improper acts,
improper relations.

26:36.630 --> 26:39.164
What does that mean?

26:39.166 --> 26:42.300
It means that we spent
every day together,

26:42.302 --> 26:45.037
until they left me
in juvenile detention

26:45.039 --> 26:46.971
for three weeks.

26:46.973 --> 26:48.973
And worse, they had
a psychologist testify

26:48.975 --> 26:50.975
that I was crazy.

26:50.977 --> 26:54.379
♪♪

26:54.381 --> 26:55.981
Wh-- what?

26:57.651 --> 26:59.852
[ Chuckles ]

26:59.854 --> 27:01.653
He made love to me.

27:01.655 --> 27:10.595
♪♪

27:10.597 --> 27:19.872
♪♪

27:19.874 --> 27:29.013
♪♪

27:29.015 --> 27:38.524
♪♪

27:43.497 --> 27:45.731
[ Birds chirping ]

27:45.733 --> 27:47.999
Ow! What?

27:48.001 --> 27:50.335
Take me home.

27:50.337 --> 27:51.737
What is it?

27:51.739 --> 27:53.605
You know, screw you, Jay!

27:53.607 --> 27:55.607
Just get me out of here.

27:55.609 --> 27:57.543
How could you do that?
How could you bring me here

27:57.545 --> 28:00.412
without telling me
what's really going on?

28:00.414 --> 28:02.348
How could you?

28:02.350 --> 28:05.284
Listen, I-I...

28:06.887 --> 28:09.788
You're a liar,
just like everybody else.

28:11.425 --> 28:14.893
I have to talk to her.
We can go home tomorrow.

28:14.895 --> 28:20.566
♪♪

28:20.568 --> 28:22.834
Is it true?

28:22.836 --> 28:25.004
Is he my father?

28:27.375 --> 28:30.642
Sometimes you catch a bad one,
Fauna.

28:30.644 --> 28:39.117
♪♪

28:39.119 --> 28:40.386
[ Car door slams ]

28:40.388 --> 28:41.387
[ Car door opens ]

28:41.389 --> 28:44.456
My whole life
has been a bad one!

28:44.458 --> 28:46.858
[ Car door closes ]

28:46.860 --> 28:49.595
♪♪

28:49.597 --> 28:54.266
All my life, I just wanted
to be something, and...

28:54.268 --> 28:57.102
I'm just made of
garbage and shit.

28:59.073 --> 29:01.873
It's all shit.

29:01.875 --> 29:04.209
Well, great.

29:06.146 --> 29:09.948
Most people,
normal people...

29:12.686 --> 29:14.820
...they don't know it.

29:14.822 --> 29:16.021
They've never seen it.

29:16.023 --> 29:18.624
They feel it,
just once at the end.

29:21.028 --> 29:23.429
You found out the truth,
Fauna.

29:23.431 --> 29:27.565
Death and evil, they're
around us all the time.

29:27.567 --> 29:32.037
And the line between us is,
um...

29:32.039 --> 29:34.706
it's thin as tissue paper.

29:34.708 --> 29:37.643
♪♪

29:37.645 --> 29:41.313
You got the bad news...

29:41.315 --> 29:44.182
and you got to know it
for the rest of your life.

29:44.184 --> 29:53.659
♪♪

29:53.661 --> 29:56.128
I hate you.

29:56.130 --> 30:05.070
♪♪

30:05.072 --> 30:09.475
♪♪

30:09.477 --> 30:12.210
Listen, I wanna, uh, I wanna
leave Fauna out of it.

30:12.212 --> 30:14.212
Peter: We got to have her.
She's the key.

30:14.214 --> 30:16.748
She's the glue.
I get it, Peter.

30:16.750 --> 30:19.818
That's the angle that
makes it work, Jay.

30:19.820 --> 30:22.087
I want to leave her out of it.
It'll ruin her.

30:22.089 --> 30:24.289
Jay, listen,
I talked you up,

30:24.291 --> 30:26.892
showed your Brody Stiles
piece around.

30:26.894 --> 30:29.294
If you can land
this Hodel thing,

30:29.296 --> 30:30.762
they're gonna move me up,
maybe,

30:30.764 --> 30:33.899
and, look, I want you as
my foreign correspondent.

30:33.901 --> 30:36.301
I'll send you to Vietnam.

30:36.303 --> 30:37.703
We want you in the mix.

30:37.705 --> 30:40.506
I think you've got the goods,
Jay, I always have.

30:40.508 --> 30:43.041
But this story has to work.

30:43.043 --> 30:45.177
Yeah.
We need the girl.

30:45.179 --> 30:47.313
[ Engine shuts off ]

30:47.315 --> 30:49.981
[ Dial tone ]
[ Sighs ]

30:49.983 --> 30:53.185
♪♪

30:53.187 --> 30:57.723
[ Indistinct talking ]

30:57.725 --> 30:59.858
Right.
Hi.

30:59.860 --> 31:02.127
Mind if I join you?

31:02.129 --> 31:04.530
What if I said yes?

31:04.532 --> 31:08.867
I'd keep asking,
like a drip.

31:08.869 --> 31:11.003
You'd better sit down, then.

31:12.672 --> 31:14.540
Sorry, guys...

31:14.542 --> 31:16.742
Come on. Let's go.
Right on.

31:16.744 --> 31:19.211
[ Indistinct talking ]

31:19.213 --> 31:21.613
[ Insects chirping ]

31:27.955 --> 31:30.022
You like it here?

31:30.024 --> 31:32.958
Boring.

31:32.960 --> 31:35.160
Beautiful but boring.

31:35.162 --> 31:38.263
The men think
they're daring.

31:39.967 --> 31:42.768
Talking about free love,
walking around naked,

31:42.770 --> 31:45.837
thinking that they're
pushing the boundaries.

31:45.839 --> 31:49.975
You know something about men
pushing boundaries, don't you?

31:49.977 --> 31:51.977
Do I?

31:51.979 --> 31:54.246
Do you?

31:55.515 --> 31:58.183
I know something
about that.

31:58.185 --> 31:59.918
Do you?

31:59.920 --> 32:02.053
I was there in '49,
Tamar.

32:02.055 --> 32:04.122
I covered your trial.

32:04.124 --> 32:07.058
Oh, yeah?
I believed you
about everything.

32:07.060 --> 32:10.662
♪♪

32:10.664 --> 32:12.330
I need your help.

32:12.332 --> 32:14.466
What you started,
you can finish.

32:14.468 --> 32:16.402
What happened to you
does not have to happen again.

32:16.404 --> 32:19.138
We can stop him.
Wh-- who?

32:20.207 --> 32:22.140
You know who.

32:22.142 --> 32:25.311
[ Laughs ]

32:27.014 --> 32:29.281
You can't.

32:29.283 --> 32:31.349
You haven't
learned yet?

32:31.351 --> 32:33.151
He's a big-wig
for the city.

32:33.153 --> 32:36.288
It's not just the police,
it's not just the movie people.

32:36.290 --> 32:39.224
The gangsters use him,
they use his clinics.

32:39.226 --> 32:41.493
They keep him safe, too.

32:41.495 --> 32:47.365
The universe...
protects George.

32:47.367 --> 32:50.368
He killed the Black Dahlia,
didn't he?

32:50.370 --> 32:52.504
Elizabeth Short?

32:52.506 --> 32:55.307
You knew it. Nobody believed
you, but you knew it.

32:55.309 --> 32:57.843
Everyone knew.

32:59.913 --> 33:02.180
We all knew it.

33:02.182 --> 33:04.650
[ Thunder rumbles ]

33:04.652 --> 33:07.252
Wait.

33:07.254 --> 33:15.393
♪♪

33:15.395 --> 33:17.395
[ Beads rattle ]

33:17.397 --> 33:21.066
"Everybody knew."
Goddamn it.

33:21.068 --> 33:24.403
[ Thunder rumbles ]

33:26.740 --> 33:28.206
[ Beads rattle ]

33:28.208 --> 33:31.009
[ Footsteps approach ]

33:31.011 --> 33:34.546
♪♪

33:34.548 --> 33:37.015
[ Thunder rumbles ]

33:37.017 --> 33:40.218
♪♪

33:40.220 --> 33:42.655
George makes these.

33:44.224 --> 33:47.459
[ Voice breaking ] He sends them
to me, and I've saved them.

33:48.696 --> 33:51.629
But you can look at these.

33:51.631 --> 33:53.832
No one knows.

33:53.834 --> 33:55.601
No one.

33:57.571 --> 34:00.238
The police thought
that they owned George.

34:00.240 --> 34:05.377
But if you own somebody...

34:05.379 --> 34:09.882
sometimes it turns out
that they own you.

34:12.452 --> 34:15.320
You'll find out.

34:15.322 --> 34:18.056
He already owns you.

34:18.058 --> 34:26.865
♪♪

34:26.867 --> 34:34.339
♪♪

34:34.341 --> 34:37.342
[ Beads rattle ]

34:37.344 --> 34:46.151
♪♪

34:46.153 --> 34:49.888
[ Thunder crashes ]

34:49.890 --> 34:53.225
Elizabeth Short...

34:53.227 --> 34:56.028
Janice Brewster...

34:56.030 --> 35:01.433
♪♪

35:01.435 --> 35:03.769
It was you, George.
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

35:03.771 --> 35:06.238
It was you.

35:06.240 --> 35:08.640
[ Thunder rumbles ]

35:10.244 --> 35:13.178
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

35:13.180 --> 35:17.683
♪♪

35:24.525 --> 35:26.825
[ Telephone rings ]

35:26.827 --> 35:29.695
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

35:33.366 --> 35:34.766
Peter: Hello?

35:34.768 --> 35:37.502
Jay: Peter, uh, I'm back.
I just got back into town.

35:37.504 --> 35:40.305
Ah. Okay.

35:40.307 --> 35:43.308
Um...let's meet.

35:43.310 --> 35:46.511
Not here.
I, uh...

35:46.513 --> 35:49.514
Ch-- Chinatown, at Ludong's.

35:49.516 --> 35:52.117
And bring the girl.

35:52.119 --> 35:54.586
She doesn't
want to do it.

35:54.588 --> 35:56.855
Just bring her, Jay.

35:56.857 --> 35:59.258
[ Dial tone ]

35:59.260 --> 36:02.327
♪♪

36:02.329 --> 36:03.995
What is this?

36:03.997 --> 36:06.865
[ Indistinct yelling ]

36:09.670 --> 36:12.604
What the hell
is going on?

36:12.606 --> 36:14.739
That's a good question.

36:14.741 --> 36:22.814
♪♪

36:22.816 --> 36:28.754
♪♪

36:28.756 --> 36:30.421
I thought you were
taking me home.

36:30.423 --> 36:33.292
Yeah, we got to make
one stop first.

36:38.431 --> 36:40.365
[ Engine shuts off ]

36:40.367 --> 36:42.968
Wait here.
I'll be back in 10 minutes.

36:42.970 --> 36:45.170
Wait for what?

36:45.172 --> 36:46.838
Just wait.

36:46.840 --> 36:52.377
♪♪

36:52.379 --> 36:54.379
[ Sighs ]

36:54.381 --> 36:58.249
♪♪

36:58.251 --> 37:03.188
There's another thing
you got to know. I'm sorry.

37:03.190 --> 37:06.225
I think George Hodel
is a murderer.

37:08.329 --> 37:11.262
And I think he killed
the Black Dahlia.

37:11.264 --> 37:15.334
♪♪

37:15.336 --> 37:17.236
I'm sorry.

37:19.473 --> 37:22.541
Sometimes you catch
a bad one, huh?

37:22.543 --> 37:29.280
♪♪

37:29.282 --> 37:30.682
10 minutes.

37:30.684 --> 37:32.684
[ Car door opens ]

37:32.686 --> 37:36.555
♪♪

37:36.557 --> 37:38.890
[ Car door closes ]

37:38.892 --> 37:42.194
[ Footsteps depart ]

37:43.364 --> 37:45.798
[ Bells chime ]

37:47.634 --> 37:50.035
[ Bells chime ]

37:50.037 --> 37:52.705
[ Bells chime ]

37:53.974 --> 37:56.307
I got it, Peter.
I got it all.

37:56.309 --> 37:58.977
Jay-bird. What the hell happened
with the rental car, amigo?

37:58.979 --> 38:01.046
Jesus,
our guy was screaming.

38:01.048 --> 38:02.447
I got notes, I got pictures.
I couldn't get her

38:02.449 --> 38:04.115
to go on record, but...
Where's the girl?

38:04.117 --> 38:05.917
...I think I've got enough.
Jay, where's the girl?

38:05.919 --> 38:07.519
I -- Did -- Did you hear
what I just said?

38:07.521 --> 38:09.454
I can prove that Hodel
killed the Dahlia. And more.

38:09.456 --> 38:11.056
He killed more women, Pete.
Wait a minute. George Hodel?

38:11.058 --> 38:13.058
He was making art,
just like his artist friends.

38:13.060 --> 38:14.860
It's all here, if you know
where to look for it. He
killed Janice Brewster, too.

38:14.862 --> 38:16.995
Wait a minute,
Janice Brewster?

38:16.997 --> 38:19.731
What are you -- what the hell
are you talking about?
Look at this, look at this.

38:19.733 --> 38:21.666
I got to develop
the Hawaii pictures...
Jay, hold up. No.

38:21.668 --> 38:23.334
...obviously from Hawaii, but --
but this one --
No, hold up.

38:23.336 --> 38:25.136
Yeah?
Hold up, we're off.

38:25.138 --> 38:26.605
I don't want to look at that.
Just hear me out.

38:26.607 --> 38:29.208
I don't want to see that
during my dinner.

38:29.210 --> 38:31.076
It'll just make me sick.
Hear me out, Peter.

38:31.078 --> 38:33.144
No, no, you were supposed to
bring the girl.

38:33.146 --> 38:35.480
Where's the girl?
You said you had the daughter.

38:35.482 --> 38:37.616
A blood test was something
that maybe might hold up.

38:37.618 --> 38:40.219
I want to leave her
out of it.
We can't, they can't.

38:40.221 --> 38:42.353
♪♪

38:42.355 --> 38:44.155
They? Wh-What are you --
What are you talking about?

38:44.157 --> 38:46.291
Who?
Wh-- who can't?

38:46.293 --> 38:49.395
What's going on, you got --
you got a rat in your soup?

38:58.371 --> 39:00.639
What?

39:00.641 --> 39:05.310
♪♪

39:05.312 --> 39:08.047
You know I was a baby reporter
with the 45th

39:08.049 --> 39:10.449
when they liberated Dachau?

39:10.451 --> 39:16.955
Jay, it was so bad,
the smell, evil of it.

39:18.859 --> 39:21.860
Evil is a live dog,
brother.

39:24.065 --> 39:26.799
[ Clears throat ]
I always thought...

39:28.135 --> 39:33.872
I always thought I'd recognize
it, you know, and fight.

39:33.874 --> 39:38.009
of course I'd fight.
I'm a good guy.

39:38.011 --> 39:41.947
♪♪

39:41.949 --> 39:43.815
But when it comes,
sometimes --

39:43.817 --> 39:46.852
sometimes when it comes,
it's slippery.

39:48.755 --> 39:51.490
Real evil is tricky, Jay.

39:53.360 --> 39:56.828
What are we talking about,
Peter? Huh?

39:56.830 --> 40:01.032
♪♪

40:01.034 --> 40:04.303
Just remember
where you are.

40:04.305 --> 40:06.305
♪♪

40:06.307 --> 40:09.508
Billis: Hey, cupcake.

40:11.044 --> 40:12.644
[ Gun cocks ]

40:12.646 --> 40:15.446
Long time no see, buddy.
How you doin'?

40:15.448 --> 40:18.984
♪♪

40:18.986 --> 40:21.787
Go on, make a run for it.

40:21.789 --> 40:24.389
You can make it.

40:24.391 --> 40:26.325
I'm sorry.

40:26.327 --> 40:30.862
♪♪

40:30.864 --> 40:34.333
Okay, come on. Get up.
Hands where I can see 'em.

40:34.335 --> 40:37.102
Let's go.

40:39.272 --> 40:41.807
[ Handcuffs clink ]

40:41.809 --> 40:44.275
I'm sorry, Jay.

40:44.277 --> 40:47.513
Yeah, well, we're all
pretty damn sorry.

40:49.150 --> 40:51.050
[ Door opens, bells chime ]

40:53.220 --> 40:55.687
[ Door closes, bells chime ]

40:55.689 --> 41:04.897
♪♪

41:07.100 --> 41:09.435
[ Car door shuts ]

41:11.839 --> 41:13.972
[ Car engine starts,
car door shuts ]

41:13.974 --> 41:20.779
♪♪

41:32.392 --> 41:34.126
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

41:34.128 --> 41:37.396
[ Dog barking ]

41:39.800 --> 41:41.567
Hello?

41:42.737 --> 41:50.009
♪♪

41:56.617 --> 41:58.150
Hello?

42:13.900 --> 42:17.002
[ Telephone ringing ]

42:26.580 --> 42:28.513
This Jimmy.

42:28.515 --> 42:30.683
Hi, Mama.

42:38.192 --> 42:40.292
I'm, uh...

42:43.998 --> 42:46.732
I-I'm sorry I had to go see her.

42:49.203 --> 42:51.570
I-I just had to.

42:53.073 --> 42:56.341
Well, then, I guess you got it
all sorted out, huh?

42:56.343 --> 42:59.478
[ Voice breaking]
It was horrible, Mama.

43:00.747 --> 43:03.282
It was just horrible.

43:05.019 --> 43:08.220
♪♪

43:08.222 --> 43:10.723
I love you, Mama.

43:12.292 --> 43:14.292
And, um...

43:14.294 --> 43:19.498
And I just --
I wanted to say thank you

43:19.500 --> 43:22.668
for taking care of me
all these years.

43:24.371 --> 43:27.772
[ Breathes shakily ]
I love you so much.

43:27.774 --> 43:31.376
And I-I won't leave you again.

43:31.378 --> 43:33.245
[ Exhales sharply ]

43:33.247 --> 43:36.781
♪♪

43:36.783 --> 43:39.984
You can call me Pat
if you want.

43:39.986 --> 43:42.187
[ Chuckles ]

43:42.189 --> 43:44.256
[ Clears throat ]

43:44.258 --> 43:46.725
Well...

43:46.727 --> 43:49.595
[ Chuckles ]

43:50.865 --> 43:54.266
...what you need to do is
get yourself home, Patta.

43:54.268 --> 43:55.934
[ Sobs ]

43:55.936 --> 43:58.002
My Patta.

43:58.004 --> 44:01.940
Don't matter who
your birth mother is.

44:01.942 --> 44:06.178
You're always gonna be
Jimmy Lee's little girl.

44:08.014 --> 44:10.282
And always will be.

44:10.284 --> 44:13.017
You're all I got,
you're all I ever...

44:13.019 --> 44:15.387
[ Laughs ]

44:16.823 --> 44:19.558
Mama, did you know
about the trial?

44:21.495 --> 44:23.896
I don't know why

44:23.898 --> 44:29.702
you keep askin' me about that,
you stupid girl?

44:29.704 --> 44:31.836
Why you keep
askin' me that?

44:31.838 --> 44:34.573
Go on and stay there, then.
Stay in Hawaii.

44:34.575 --> 44:36.909
Good riddance
to bad rubbish!

44:36.911 --> 44:39.377
No Mama, I-I'm --
I ain't in Hawaii anymore.

44:39.379 --> 44:41.713
I'm in Los Angeles.
You ain't never got
to come back here,

44:41.715 --> 44:44.416
as far as I'm concerned.
No, no --

44:45.920 --> 44:49.855
♪♪

44:52.993 --> 44:54.893
Hey, Pretty Jimmy.

44:56.530 --> 44:59.398
What's got you so blue?

45:01.068 --> 45:03.602
Fauna's in Hawaii?

45:05.272 --> 45:07.272
It seems.

45:07.274 --> 45:09.575
[ Chuckles nervously ]

45:12.012 --> 45:14.212
I'll get you a drink.

45:14.214 --> 45:16.448
I brought wine.

45:18.218 --> 45:20.418
Well, bring it on in.

45:20.420 --> 45:22.220
[ Bottle lid opens ]

45:22.222 --> 45:23.756
[ Liquid pours ]

45:23.758 --> 45:26.759
I was just making
myself a steak.

45:28.095 --> 45:30.629
You like yours...

45:32.299 --> 45:33.966
...rare?

45:33.968 --> 45:36.034
Please.

45:36.036 --> 45:43.342
♪♪

46:09.269 --> 46:11.670
Terrible, Jimmy.

46:11.672 --> 46:14.406
You're only
as good as your tools.

46:15.542 --> 46:17.810
[ Drawer closes, opens ]

46:17.812 --> 46:19.478
Ah.

46:19.480 --> 46:22.147
Well, at least...

46:22.149 --> 46:25.750
♪♪

46:25.752 --> 46:28.821
I'm sorry I missed Fauna
in Los Angeles,

46:28.823 --> 46:31.756
but it never seemed to be
quite the right time.

46:31.758 --> 46:33.958
Oh, these knives are piss-poor,
Jimmy.

46:33.960 --> 46:36.161
There's only so much
I can do.

46:36.163 --> 46:37.562
[ Drawer opens ]

46:37.564 --> 46:39.231
[ Metal clanks ]

46:39.233 --> 46:41.766
[ Drawer closes ]

46:41.768 --> 46:47.372
♪♪

46:47.374 --> 46:48.973
[ Lock clicks ]

46:48.975 --> 46:55.380
♪♪

46:55.382 --> 46:57.716
I'm worried about you,
Jimmy.

46:57.718 --> 47:01.920
Alone out here,
Fauna running wild.

47:01.922 --> 47:07.592
And now she's hooked up
with some cretin reporter,

47:07.594 --> 47:12.598
and my friend, my protégé
is dead.

47:14.268 --> 47:16.334
It's confusing.

47:16.336 --> 47:19.003
[ Breathes shakily ]

47:19.005 --> 47:22.941
♪♪

47:22.943 --> 47:27.245
You've always been good at
keeping secrets, Pretty Jimmy.

47:28.215 --> 47:30.348
[ Pounding on door ]
Stanley: Hey, Jimmy Lee!

47:30.350 --> 47:31.950
Where you at, girl?!

47:31.952 --> 47:33.285
Help me!

47:33.287 --> 47:35.354
Help me!

47:35.356 --> 47:37.021
Hardly sporting, Jimmy.

47:37.023 --> 47:38.490
Stanley!

47:38.492 --> 47:40.092
Stanley!

47:40.094 --> 47:42.628
[ Moaning ]

47:44.298 --> 47:47.432
Oh, God!
What the hell, man?

47:47.434 --> 47:50.502
Jimmy Lee, hold up.

47:52.306 --> 47:59.244
♪ Midnight, you heavy, leaden ♪

47:59.246 --> 48:02.847
♪ It's midnight ♪

48:02.849 --> 48:10.389
♪ Come on and trade in
your old dreams for new ♪

48:10.391 --> 48:15.994
♪ Your new dreams for old ♪

48:15.996 --> 48:20.465
♪ I know where they're bought ♪

48:20.467 --> 48:26.471
♪ I know where they're sold ♪

48:26.473 --> 48:30.008
♪ Midnight ♪

48:30.010 --> 48:38.350
♪ You've got to
get there at midnight ♪

48:38.352 --> 48:47.692
♪ And you'll be met there
by others like you ♪

48:47.694 --> 48:52.897
♪ Brothers as blue ♪

48:52.899 --> 49:00.172
♪ Smiling on the street ♪

49:00.174 --> 49:01.707
♪ A dream ♪

49:07.514 --> 49:13.319
♪♪

49:16.390 --> 49:25.664
♪♪

49:28.202 --> 49:34.907
♪♪

49:37.077 --> 49:44.183
♪♪

49:45.752 --> 49:55.160
♪♪
